  "original_title": "Sri Lanka Treasury bill yields down, TT dollars unchanged",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka Treasury bill yields down, TT dollars unchanged",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka\u2019s Treasury bill yields were down Friday after hitting record high before rate hike while a guidance peg on interbank spot trading was strengthened, dealers said.",
        "The three months\u2019 bill was quoted at 28.00/30 percent Friday down from 29.00/30 percent Thursday.",
        "The six-month Treasury bill was quoted at 28.30/29.00 percent, down from 28.75/29.25 percent .",
        "The one-year Treasury bill was quoted at 28.30/29.00 percent, also down from 29.00/30.",
        "After the initial auction on July 06, Sri Lanka has raised 17.5 billion rupees from sales of Treasury bills at weighted average yields on a tap issue",
        "A guidance peg announced by Sri Lanka\u2019s central bank for interbank transactions appreciated by 47 to 360.35 against the US dollar on July 08 from the previous day\u2019s 360.82, data showed on Friday.",
        "The commercial banks offered dollars for telegraphic transfers at rates between 366.79 and 370.00 for small transactions on July 07, steady from Wednesday, commercial bank data showed.",
        "Banks offered to buy inward remittances at 356.50 -359.00 rupees, also steady from the previous day. (Colombo/July 08/2022)"
      ],
